#. <section class="sutta" id="sn10.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga"
msgstr "1. With Indaka"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Sūcilomasutta"
msgstr "3. With Spiky"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.207"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gayāyaṃ viharati ṭaṅkitamañce sūcilomassa yakkhassa "
"bhavane."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Gayā on the cut-stone ledge in the "
"haunt of Spiky the native spirit."

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kharo ca yakkho sūcilomo ca yakkho bhagavato avidūre "
"atikkamanti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the native spirits Shaggy and Spiky were passing by not far "
"from the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho kharo yakkho sūcilomaṃ yakkhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So Shaggy said to Spiky:"

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.4"
msgid "“eso samaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“That’s an ascetic.”"

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.5"
msgid "“Neso samaṇo, samaṇako eso."
msgstr "“That’s no ascetic, he’s a faker!"

msgctxt "sn10.3:1.6"
msgid "Yāva jānāmi yadi vā so samaṇo yadi vā pana so samaṇako”ti."
msgstr "I’ll soon find out whether he’s an ascetic or a faker.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.446"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sūcilomo yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato "
"kāyaṃ upanāmesi."
msgstr "Then Spiky went up to the Buddha and leaned up against his body,"

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā kāyaṃ apanāmesi."
msgstr "but the Buddha drew back."

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho sūcilomo yakkho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Spiky said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.4"
msgid "“bhāyasi maṃ, samaṇā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you afraid, ascetic?”"

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.5"
msgid "“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, bhāyāmi;"
msgstr "“No, sir, I’m not afraid."

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.6"
msgid "api ca te samphasso pāpako”ti."
msgstr "But your touch is bad.”"

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.7"
msgid "“Pañhaṃ taṃ, samaṇa, pucchissāmi."
msgstr "“I will ask you a question, ascetic."

# Considering the Ganges is 100km away, this is even more impressive!
#. VAR: pāragaṅgāya → pāraṃ gaṅgāya (mr)
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.8"
msgid ""
"Sace me na byākarissasi, cittaṃ vā te khipissāmi, hadayaṃ vā te phālessāmi, "
"pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"If you don’t answer me, I’ll drive you insane, or explode your heart, or "
"grab you by the feet and throw you to the far shore of the Ganges!”"

msgctxt "sn10.3:2.9"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo me cittaṃ vā khipeyya hadayaṃ "
"vā phāleyya pādesu vā gahetvā pāragaṅgāya khipeyya;"
msgstr ""
"“I don’t see anyone in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans who could do "
"that to me."

#. VAR: () → (atha kho sūcilomo yakkho bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi.) (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.3:2.10"
msgid "api ca tvaṃ, āvuso, puccha yadā kaṅkhasī”ti. ()"
msgstr "But anyway, ask what you wish.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc808"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.1"
msgid "“Rāgo ca doso ca kutonidānā,"
msgstr "“Where do greed and hate come from?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.2"
msgid "Aratī ratī lomahaṃso kutojā;"
msgstr "From where do discontent, desire, and terror spring?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.3"
msgid "Kuto samuṭṭhāya manovitakkā,"
msgstr "Where do the mind’s thoughts originate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:3.4"
msgid "Kumārakā dhaṅkamivossajantī”ti."
msgstr "like a crow let loose by boys.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc809"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.1"
msgid "“Rāgo ca doso ca itonidānā,"
msgstr "“Greed and hate come from here;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.2"
msgid "Aratī ratī lomahaṃso itojā;"
msgstr "from here spring discontent, desire, and terror;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.3"
msgid "Ito samuṭṭhāya manovitakkā,"
msgstr "here’s where the mind’s thoughts originate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:4.4"
msgid "Kumārakā dhaṅkamivossajanti."
msgstr "like a crow let loose by boys."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.447"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc810"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.1"
msgid "Snehajā attasambhūtā,"
msgstr "Born of affection, originating in oneself,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.2"
msgid "nigrodhasseva khandhajā;"
msgstr "like the shoots from a banyan’s trunk;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.3"
msgid "Puthū visattā kāmesu,"
msgstr "the many kinds of attachment to sensual pleasures"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vitatā → vitthatā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn10.3:5.4"
msgid "māluvāva vitatā vane."
msgstr "are like camel’s foot creeper strung through the woods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.208"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc811"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.1"
msgid "Ye naṃ pajānanti yatonidānaṃ,"
msgstr "Those who understand where they come from"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.2"
msgid "Te naṃ vinodenti suṇohi yakkha;"
msgstr "get rid of them—listen up, spirit!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.3"
msgid "Te duttaraṃ oghamimaṃ taranti,"
msgstr "They cross this flood so hard to cross,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.3:6.4"
msgid "Atiṇṇapubbaṃ apunabbhavāyā”ti."
msgstr "not crossed before, so as to not be reborn.”"
